<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-1" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-1</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/friendship-for" mutual="https://usaybia.net/person/1911 https://usaybia.net/person/926">
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah</persName> and
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/926">Ibn Abī Uṣaybiʿah</persName> met several times and had sympathy for each other.
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">2</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-2" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-2</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/teacher-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/338"><!-- the other way around!-->
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/338">Abū Saʿīd ibn Abī Sulaymān</persName>, the  uncle of 
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah</persName> taught him the art of medicine.<!-- where?-->
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">2</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-3" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-3</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/teacher-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1594">
         <desc>
            Later, <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/"><!-- ID??-->Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah</persName> studied medicine under
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">al-Dakhwār</persName>, <!-- no comma before who or which -->who also was the teacher of <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/926">Ibn Abī Uṣaybiʿah</persName>.
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">2</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="event" xml:id="factoid-4" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-4</idno>
   <listEvent>
      <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/aquitance"><!-- acquaintance!-->
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1472">al-Malik al-Kāmil</persName> met 
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah</persName> in a bathhouse in 
            <placeName ref="https://usaybia.net/place/482">al-Ruhā </placeName>.
            <choice>
            <!--<reg><date when="1053" calendar="julian">1053</date></reg>
                            <orig><date when-custom="445"
                                datingMethod="hijri">445</date></orig>-->
               <reg>
                  <date notBefore="1200" notAfter="" calendar="#julian"></date>
               </reg>
               <orig>
                  <date when="" calendar="#hijri">598</date>
               </orig>
            </choice>
            <listRelation>
               <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/" active="https://usaybia.net/person/257" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1472"></relation>
            </listRelation>Abū l-Khayr ibn Abī Sulaymān Dāwūd, the father of Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah got the advise from al-Malik al-Kāmil to make his son a doctor instead of a knight.
         </desc>
      </event>
   </listEvent>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">3</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-5" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-5</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/patron-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1472"><!-- the other way around-->
         <desc>
           When <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqah</persName> 
           was sent to 
           <placename ref="https://usaybia.net/place/121">Cairo</placename>
            in <choice>
              <reg>
                 <date notBefore="" notAfter="" calendar="#julian">1202-1203</date>
              </reg>
              <orig>
                 <date when="" calendar="#hijri">599</date>
              </orig>
           </choice> he was held in high regard and under 
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1472">al-Malik al-Kāmil</persName> and received numerous gifts and his trust in medical matters.
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">3</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-6" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-6</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/patron-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1493"><!-- the other way around-->
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/"><!-- ID??-->Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqa</persName> served under the son of al-Malik al-Kāmil
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1493">al-Malik al-Ṣāliḥ Najm al-Dīn Ayyūb</persName>. 
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">3</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-7" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-7</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/patron-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1481"><!--other way around-->
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqa</persName> served the son of al-Malik al-Ṣāliḥ Najm al-Dīn Ayyūb
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1481">al-Malik al-Muʿaẓẓam Tūrānshāh</persName> until he was killed in <choice>
               <reg>
                  <date notBefore="" notAfter="" calendar="#julian">01-05-1250</date>
               </reg>
               <orig>
                  <date when="" calendar="#hijri">648</date>
               </orig>
            </choice>. 
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">3</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-8" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-8</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/patron-of" active="https://usaybia.net/person/1911" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1496"><!--other way around-->
         <desc>
            After the death of al-Malik al-Muʿaẓẓam Tūrānshāh<!-- with Pers-tag--> <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqa</persName> served 
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1496">al-Malik al-Ẓāhir Rukn al-Dīn</persName> under the turkish dynasty where he was bestowed for his knowledge and held in honour. 
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">3</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

<ab type="factoid" subtype="relation" xml:id="factoid-9" resp="#mtolay">
   <idno type="URI">https://usaybia.net/factoid/14-54-9</idno>
   <listRelation>
      <relation type="person" ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/?" active="https://usaybia.net/person/" passive="https://usaybia.net/person/1472">
         <desc>
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1472">al-Malik al-Kāmil</persName> gave 
            <persName ref="https://usaybia.net/person/1911">Rashīd al-Dīn Abū Ḥulayqa</persName> his name because of his earring he was wearing 
            <!-- nice :D can we rephrase this? how about: al malik gave Rashid al-Din the nickname Hulayqa because of the ring he used to wear on his ear (?) -->
            <choice>
               <reg>
                  <date notBefore="" notAfter="" calendar="#julian"></date>
               </reg>
               <orig>
                  <date when="" calendar="#hijri"></date>
               </orig>
            </choice>. 
         </desc>
      </relation>
   </listRelation>
   <bibl type="urn">
      <ptr target="urn:cts:arabicLit:0668IbnAbiUsaibia.Tabaqatalatibba.lhom-ed-ara1:14.54"></ptr>
      <citedRange unit="part">4</citedRange>
   </bibl>
</ab>

